<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 11:20AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTION IS ADVISED FOR REDUCED VISIBILITY IN AREAS OF FOG INTO
EARLY THIS AFTERNOON...
WEATHER...
*  Areas of fog, locally dense, will continue into the early
afternoon hours. Visibility may be restricted below 1/2 mile
at times.
IMPACTS...
* Reduced visibility in areas of fog will make travel difficult
at times.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for hazardous
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time in
areas of reduced visibility. Use low beam headlights and extra
spacing in between vehicles.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
